OL,3,CCharity boss warns of dire famine in
OL,4,CEthiopia
OL,6,F"We've heard accounts of children who
OL,7,Fno longer feel the pain from hunger
OL,8,Fpangs, not because they have eaten,
OL,9,Fbut because they don't have the energy
OL,10,Fto feel pain anymore.
OL,12,F"It's hard not to make comparisons
OL,13,Fbetween how the world was so moved to
OL,14,Fact nearly 40 years ago when Ethiopia
OL,15,Fwas gripped by the infamous famine of
OL,16,Fthe 80s and the situation today that
OL,17,Fis virtually being ignored. We need to
OL,18,Fmake sure that the terrible outcome
OL,19,FTigray is heading for doesn't happen,
OL,20,Fbut it will if we don't act now."
